<li><a href="/wiki/Moondial" title="Moondial">Moondial</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Nocturnal_(instrument)" title="Nocturnal (instrument)">Nocturnal</a> — device for determining time by the stars at night.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Scottish_sundial" title="Scottish sundial">Scottish sundial</a> — the ancient renaissance sundials of Scotland.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Tide_(time)" title="Tide (time)">Tide (time)</a> — devisions of the day on early sundials.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Wilan%C3%B3w_Palace#The_sundial" title="Wilanów Palace">Wilanów Palace Sundial</a>, created by <a href="/wiki/Johannes_Hevelius" title="Johannes Hevelius">Johannes Hevelius</a> in about 1684.</li>
</ul>
