<li id="cite_note-58"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cadran_bifilaire" class="external text" title="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cadran_bifilaire" rel="nofollow">cadran bifilaire</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-59"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59" title="">^</a></b> Rohr (1965), pp. 114–115.</li>
<li id="cite_note-60"><b><a href="#cite_ref-60" title="">^</a></b> Waugh (1973), pp. 18–28.</li>
<li id="cite_note-61"><b><a href="#cite_ref-61" title="">^</a></b> Mayall and Mayall, p. 26.</li>
<li id="cite_note-thayer-62"><b><a href="#cite_ref-thayer_62-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Vitruvius/9*.html#refK" class="external text" title="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Vitruvius/9*.html#refK" rel="nofollow">"Marcus Vitruvius Pollio:de Architectura, Book IX"</a>. The Latin text is that of the Teubner edition of 1899 by Valentin Rose, transcribed by Bill Thayer. 2007-07-07<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Vitruvius/9*.html#refK" class="external free" title="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Vitruvius/9*.html#refK" rel="nofollow">http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Vitruvius/9*.html#refK</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-09-07</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Marcus+Vitruvius+Pollio%3Ade+Architectura%2C+Book+IX&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2007-07-07&amp;rft.pub=The+Latin+text+is+that+of+the+Teubner+edition+of+1899+by+Valentin+Rose%2C+transcribed+by+Bill+Thayer&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fpenelope.uchicago.edu%2FThayer%2FE%2FRoman%2FTexts%2FVitruvius%2F9%2A.html%23refK&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Sundial"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-63"><b><a href="#cite_ref-63" title="">^</a></b> Edmund Buchner, "Solarium Augusti und <a href="/wiki/Ara_Pacis" title="Ara Pacis">Ara Pacis</a>", <i>Römische Mitteilungen</i> <b>83</b> (1976:319-75); <i>Die Sonnenuhr des Augustus: Kaiser Augustus und die verlorene Republik</i> (Berlin) 1988.</li>
<li id="cite_note-64"><b><a href="#cite_ref-64" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.nmm.ac.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.353" class="external text" title="http://www.nmm.ac.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.353" rel="nofollow">"History of the sundial"</a>. <a href="/wiki/National_Maritime_Museum" title="National Maritime Museum">National Maritime Museum</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nmm.ac.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.353" class="external free" title="http://www.nmm.ac.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.353" rel="nofollow">http://www.nmm.ac.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.353</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-07-02</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+sundial&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BNational+Maritime+Museum%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nmm.ac.uk%2Fserver%2Fshow%2FconWebDoc.353&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Sundial"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
